1
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:21,048
- All right, that'll be $3.40.
- Oh, okay. Let me just...

2
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,562
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

3
00:00:35,435 --> 00:00:37,404
And here you go.

4
00:00:41,842 --> 00:00:43,435
And there you go.

5
00:00:43,510 --> 00:00:45,240
- Thank you.
- No worries.

6
00:00:46,313 --> 00:00:47,611
Thank you very much.

7
00:00:57,958 --> 00:00:59,950
- Have you seen my ID badge?
- No.

8
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,619
I had it last night.

9
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:05,096
But maybe it fell out of my
bag when I paid for the pizza.

10
00:01:05,198 --> 00:01:07,963
This wouldn't happen
if you stayed over.

11
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,094
If you'll remember back
to when I lived here,

12
00:01:10,203 --> 00:01:13,196
my ability to lose things
has always been top-notch.

13
00:01:13,273 --> 00:01:16,573
If you stayed over, you wouldn't
have had to come all the way back here

14
00:01:16,643 --> 00:01:18,612
- when you realized...
- It's too soon, Shaun.

15
00:01:18,679 --> 00:01:20,079
Why?

16
00:01:21,281 --> 00:01:24,376
If I stayed over, we both
would've gotten a lot less sleep.

17
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:26,215
Why is it too soon?

18
00:01:26,286 --> 00:01:28,585
We've only been
together a few weeks.

19
00:01:28,655 --> 00:01:33,218
How many weeks of being together
are required before you can stay over?

20
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:34,556
Yes!

21
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:42,366
Saturday. I will spend
the night Saturday.

22
00:01:52,312 --> 00:01:54,110
I'm glad we come here.

23
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,141
I don't want to stop coming.

24
00:01:58,085 --> 00:02:00,919
- Why would we?
- I don't know, that's the way it works.

25
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:04,617
You mourn, you cry,
and then you forget.

26
00:02:08,929 --> 00:02:11,296
You don't forget. You...

27
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,526
start to move on.

28
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:20,134
I don't want to stop coming.

29
00:02:31,618 --> 00:02:34,918
Your temperature is almost
101. Your other symptoms?

30
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:39,119
First, it was a sore throat,
then my body started aching.

31
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:44,624
And then there's this
cough. I even had my flu shot.

32
00:02:44,698 --> 00:02:47,497
Unfortunately, influenza
is constantly mutating,

33
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:49,229
the shot always lags behind.

34
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:51,999
Hopefully, you'll recover
faster because of it.

35
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:57,800
My daughter's very worried that I
might have this virus from China?

36
00:02:57,878 --> 00:02:58,878
What's it called?

37
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:02,347
Have you been to China or been around
anyone who's been to China recently?

38
00:03:03,383 --> 00:03:04,749
Taken any cruises?

39
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:08,014
The coronavirus doesn't
cause sore throats.

40
00:03:08,088 --> 00:03:09,386
This is a bad case of the flu.

41
00:03:09,456 --> 00:03:13,757
Go home, rest, drink plenty of
fluids. You'll be fine in a week or two.

42
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:25,702
The virus damaged
your mother's lungs.

43
00:03:25,772 --> 00:03:27,832
Her body is working
harder to breathe,

44
00:03:27,908 --> 00:03:30,173
but her blood oxygen
levels continue to drop.

45
00:03:30,243 --> 00:03:32,735
She definitely has Corona?

46
00:03:35,282 --> 00:03:37,842
We're doing everything
we can to help her.

47
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:03,737
You have COVID-19.

48
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:05,438
But you haven't tested me.

49
00:04:05,545 --> 00:04:08,413
Your chest X-ray suggests
ground-glass opacities.

50
00:04:08,482 --> 00:04:12,249
That's COVID. I don't need a test.
Which is good because we don't have any.

51
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:13,412
But I can't smell.

52
00:04:13,487 --> 00:04:16,150
I've read about it.
That's not a symptom.

53
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:20,125
I guess it is now.
You have COVID.

54
00:04:23,797 --> 00:04:25,163
Okay. Now what?

55
00:04:25,232 --> 00:04:27,565
Now, you go home.

56
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:29,296
- That's it?
- That's it.

57
00:04:29,369 --> 00:04:31,235
There's no treatment,
stay away from people.

58
00:04:31,304 --> 00:04:33,466
Come back if you have
trouble breathing. Goodbye.

59
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:37,674
Twenty-five tests? Per day?

60
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,038
No, just give me
one of tomorrow's.

61
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:44,610
Hello? County Health Department.
I don't have time for them,

62
00:04:44,684 --> 00:04:46,312
and they don't have time for me.

63
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:47,682
Patient.

64
00:04:47,754 --> 00:04:50,121
- Needs a lumpectomy?
- Yes. Needs. And yet.

65
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:52,159
- Surgery canceled?
- They ruled it elective.

66
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:54,524
- It is.
- You just said "needs."

67
00:04:54,594 --> 00:04:57,291
I didn't say when. This can
wait till after the pandemic.

68
00:04:59,332 --> 00:05:03,099
Yeah, I'm twice the size of SJ General.
I should have twice the amount of tests.

69
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,934
Well, who do I speak to?

70
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:07,236
Do you feel shortness of breath?

71
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,502
A little.

72
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:12,779
If I'm sick, is my baby sick?

73
00:05:12,846 --> 00:05:15,372
This disease doesn't really
seem to affect children or babies

74
00:05:15,482 --> 00:05:18,213
like it does adults.
Should we admit her?

75
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:20,481
She's probably safer at home.

76
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,958
What's at home? Do you
have a support system?

77
00:05:25,025 --> 00:05:27,893
Can anyone come help
you, in case you get worse?

78
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:31,192
It's just me and the little one.

79
00:05:35,035 --> 00:05:37,698
Get her a room. Start her
on oxygen via nasal cannula,

80
00:05:37,804 --> 00:05:40,330
and let's try some
vancomycin and cefepime.

81
00:05:41,141 --> 00:05:44,703
Hey, Mia. No, I'm not headed
back there today. Or this week.

82
00:05:44,811 --> 00:05:46,143
I found a temporary place here.

83
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:47,909
<i>There are hospitals
in Phoenix too.</i>

84
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,983
If I come home, do you
want me living with you?

85
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,541
<i>That's the point.</i>

86
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:53,643
Every night after 12
hours of COVID patients,

87
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:56,622
to hang out with you. And
Kellan. And his asthma.

88
00:05:58,692 --> 00:06:01,821
<i>He's gonna be really
bummed. His graduation...</i>

89
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:04,831
Isn't till June, this'll be
over long before then.

90
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:07,527
<i>Someone must have connections.</i>

91
00:06:07,634 --> 00:06:11,662
<i>At county? Van Kleek does, Woo
does, Nguyen's husband works at...</i>

92
00:06:11,738 --> 00:06:12,865
<i>Get one of them to call.</i>

93
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,170
<i>The board of every
hospital has connections.</i>

94
00:06:15,242 --> 00:06:17,370
<i>They're calling Public
Health and getting nowhere.</i>

95
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:20,346
<i>- So we do nothing?
- No. We do everything we can.</i>

96
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:22,575
<i>We hammer at official channels</i>

97
00:06:22,682 --> 00:06:25,049
<i>and every manufacturer's
rep that we deal with</i>

98
00:06:25,118 --> 00:06:27,781
<i>and see what companies,
if any, have undisturbed...</i>

99
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:29,254
<i>Nuts or no nuts?</i>

100
00:06:30,423 --> 00:06:31,423
<i>Uh...</i>

101
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:37,455
<i>I'm sorry, I'm in the middle
of a meeting with the board.</i>

102
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:41,695
<i>Hey, everyone. I'm just
making banana bread.</i>

103
00:06:41,768 --> 00:06:44,397
Let's just take a...
I'll take a quick break.

104
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:49,034
If someone can get me a list of
PPE suppliers in the area, thanks.

105
00:06:49,109 --> 00:06:50,236
I'll be back.

106
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:53,441
I don't want banana bread. I
want to be back at the hospital.

107
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:55,778
I'm the president and
I'm at home, watching.

108
00:06:55,849 --> 00:06:57,044
You're doing your job.

109
00:06:57,117 --> 00:07:00,110
And whatever you gotta do,
whatever decisions you need to make,

110
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:01,313
you just do it right here.

111
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:06,793
I can take the necessary precautions,
that whole meeting was about PPEs,

112
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:09,591
- mitigation...
- Aaron, you are 65 years old

113
00:07:09,663 --> 00:07:14,067
with a history of cancer.
You get that virus, then what?

114
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:18,099
I don't know what I'm doing.

115
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:22,302
You're being smart, you're being
safe. What is wrong with that?

116
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:26,642
And what is wrong with being
home together for a while?

117
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,278
Nothing, I guess.

118
00:07:31,351 --> 00:07:35,083
We have no
choice. Let's enjoy it.

119
00:07:36,856 --> 00:07:38,848
Nuts or no nuts?

120
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:42,623
- Nuts.
- Okay.

121
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:47,797
What's going on?

122
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:49,836
Your mother's oxygen
got critically low,

123
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:52,668
- we need to get her on a ventilator.
- That'll help her get better?

124
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:56,198
It'll keep her alive, hopefully long
enough for her to fight off the virus.

125
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:58,677
- Is it dangerous?
- More for us.

126
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:04,877
She's out.

127
00:08:10,790 --> 00:08:11,985
Lots of swelling.

128
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,464
Slow. You want this over
with as soon as possible.

129
00:08:24,537 --> 00:08:26,768
But you also don't
want her to cough.

130
00:08:55,835 --> 00:08:56,859
Hello.

131
00:08:56,936 --> 00:08:59,235
<i>Sorry. I woke you. Thought
you had to be up now.</i>

132
00:08:59,305 --> 00:09:01,865
- I do. I pushed snooze twice.
<i>- I read the numbers.</i>

133
00:09:01,941 --> 00:09:04,433
<i>You guys had seven deaths in
Santa Clara County yesterday.</i>

134
00:09:04,511 --> 00:09:05,672
<i>Any at St. Bonaventure?</i>

135
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:08,214
We have deaths at St.
Bonaventure every day, Kellan.

136
00:09:08,314 --> 00:09:11,580
- <i>I miss you.</i>
- I know. You already said that.

137
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:13,085
<i>I wanted to reinforce the point.</i>

138
00:09:13,153 --> 00:09:16,885
You said you missed me a
lot. And we're together right now.

139
00:09:16,956 --> 00:09:19,221
<i>It's different not
being actually together.</i>

140
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:21,454
You mean not being
able to have sex?

141
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:25,522
Haven't been tested
because there's no need.

142
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:26,930
I'm fine. No symptoms.

143
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,866
<i>You can be asymptomatic
and still have it.</i>

144
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:31,097
I know. You still working out?

145
00:09:31,171 --> 00:09:33,333
Don't want to lose arm
strength while you're off.

146
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:34,601
<i>I'm making a salad.</i>

147
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,473
<i>Figured I'd bring it by and we'll
have a masked, distanced dinner.</i>

148
00:09:37,544 --> 00:09:39,479
You can't eat with a mask on.

149
00:09:39,546 --> 00:09:42,209
<i>We'll take them off when
we're eating, and turn our heads.</i>

150
00:09:42,282 --> 00:09:45,810
- Regular masks don't work.
<i>- Bring me one from work.</i>

151
00:09:45,885 --> 00:09:46,784
No.

152
00:09:46,853 --> 00:09:48,412
<i>Do you have enough PPE?</i>

153
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:51,924
- PPE?
<i>- Personal protective equipment, Dad.</i>

154
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:56,156
Someone's been doing their research.
We have enough. I'm being careful.

155
00:09:56,563 --> 00:10:00,091
- I heard your mother joined a book club.
<i>- Is Shaun being careful?</i>

156
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:02,158
Oh, yes, I am. Very.

157
00:10:02,235 --> 00:10:05,000
<i>So am I. It should be
safe for me to come over.</i>

158
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:07,870
You can't come over
because we are being safe.

159
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,672
<i>What about apples? Do you have
enough apples? I could go shop...</i>

160
00:10:10,743 --> 00:10:11,972
He does.

161
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:15,675
- Everything is under control.
- Everything is under control.

162
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:25,925
I told you not to come back
unless your breathing got worse.

163
00:10:25,992 --> 00:10:28,792
<i>Between the fever and the
cough, he's barely sleeping.</i>

164
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,630
Who said that?

165
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:36,197
My wife wanted to come
with me, but she has to work.

166
00:10:36,269 --> 00:10:37,862
She's essential personnel.

167
00:10:38,538 --> 00:10:40,404
<i>He's lost ten pounds.</i>

168
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:42,774
Breathe.

169
00:10:43,176 --> 00:10:44,667
<i>He should have
come in a week ago.</i>

170
00:10:44,744 --> 00:10:47,213
Please don't talk
when I'm listening.

171
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:50,343
Breathe.

172
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:53,944
<i>He's also coughing. A lot.
He hasn't told you, but he is.</i>

173
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:57,617
- I'm sorry.
<i>- Did you just apologize for me?</i>

174
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:59,454
<i>Because I'm worried?</i>

175
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:03,489
<i>So sorry. I'm a wife who is
worried about her husband.</i>

176
00:11:03,563 --> 00:11:07,466
<i>- Forgive me, I'm evil.</i>
- It's lucky that you're so irritating.

177
00:11:08,635 --> 00:11:09,967
<i>What?</i>

178
00:11:10,036 --> 00:11:13,632
Your husband's blood
oxygen level is dangerously low.

179
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:16,670
That can't be.

180
00:11:16,743 --> 00:11:20,373
I mean, I don't feel that bad.
Not great, but my breathing...

181
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:24,747
That's interesting. You don't
feel bad, but you are. Hm.

182
00:11:24,817 --> 00:11:26,251
Admit him to the COVID floor,

183
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:29,915
start heated humidified
high-flow nasal cannula at 8 LPM.

184
00:11:52,011 --> 00:11:54,708
Her CRP, ESR, ferritin, D-dimer,

185
00:11:54,781 --> 00:11:57,478
transaminases, and
IL-6 are all way up.

186
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,542
Try her on dexamethasone.

187
00:11:59,619 --> 00:12:01,212
I read in my online
physicians' group

188
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:03,552
that the UK's had
some success with that.

189
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:07,759
Thank you.

190
00:12:08,261 --> 00:12:10,696
Sorry. What did you say?
Couldn't hear with the mask.

191
00:12:11,764 --> 00:12:14,427
Thank you. I heard you
stepped in for a therapist

192
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,934
that didn't come in today.

193
00:12:16,002 --> 00:12:18,870
My son has asthma. I've been
doing this kind of stuff for years.

194
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:26,477
I got a dresser and a crib,
bolted them both to the wall.

195
00:12:28,147 --> 00:12:32,642
All that matters is her. I'm
going to do everything right.

196
00:12:34,387 --> 00:12:37,448
You're going to be a parent. No
way you're doing everything right.

197
00:12:43,896 --> 00:12:47,298
Even trade, 200 surplus
vials for your COVID test kits.

198
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:49,268
What do you need?

199
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:53,534
I've got hydroxychloroquine,
ribavirin... EKG leads?

200
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:56,303
No, no, I'm not saying no.
We'll pick them up in two hours.

201
00:12:56,376 --> 00:12:58,277
We have a surplus of EKG leads?

202
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:01,075
No. We've got a shortage. But
that's a problem that can wait.

203
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:04,140
Mildred's P-to-F is below 50, she's
showing signs of cardiogenic shock.

204
00:13:04,217 --> 00:13:05,913
- Start her on steroids.
- Already have.

205
00:13:05,985 --> 00:13:07,920
If she goes downhill,
I'd like to add ECMO,

206
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:10,616
- take the strain off her heart and lungs.
- Good idea.

207
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,284
I need EKG leads,
what do you need?

208
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:19,457
- Should we intubate him?
- Not yet. Not a minute before we need to.

209
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:21,933
His oxygen saturation has
been dropping steadily...

210
00:13:22,001 --> 00:13:23,479
- It's 74 now.
- At this rate...

211
00:13:23,503 --> 00:13:27,463
We're gonna prone him. Buddy in
New York says it helps. Sometimes.

212
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:43,720
How is Claire feeling?

213
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:48,284
I assume she's exhausted.

214
00:13:48,361 --> 00:13:50,523
That isn't a feeling.
How is she feeling?

215
00:13:50,596 --> 00:13:53,430
It's a little tough to tell,
Shaun. She's wearing a mask.

216
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:57,300
Exactly. You can't tell if
she's happy or if she's sad,

217
00:13:57,370 --> 00:14:00,135
you can't tell if I'm
sad or if I'm happy.

218
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:01,902
You seem distressingly happy.

219
00:14:01,974 --> 00:14:05,103
It's exciting. I can't read people,
now no one can read people.

220
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:08,114
We're all forced to rely
on more reliable markers,

221
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:09,649
like what people are saying.

222
00:14:09,716 --> 00:14:12,481
Since you can't tell from
my face, I'll use my words.

223
00:14:12,552 --> 00:14:14,817
I feel terrible, we
all feel terrible.

224
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:17,982
Because we spent the last 18
hours watching people get sicker,

225
00:14:18,057 --> 00:14:20,925
we didn't help anyone, we just
fended off death for a little while.

226
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:24,156
We're all pretty disgusted at the
joy you're taking from this situation.

227
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:26,392
- Give him a break.
- You're enjoying this too.

228
00:14:26,499 --> 00:14:30,527
All elective surgeries have been
canceled so no one is a surgeon anymore,

229
00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:32,071
- not just you.
- Claire...

230
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:36,936
We're all exhausted. And
tomorrow won't be any different.

231
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:40,537
But it'd help if we didn't hate
each other when that time comes.

